==English==
* A directive is an instruction or guideline that indicates how to perform an action or reach a goal.
* A directive is also an authoritative decision from an official body, which may or may not have binding force.
** In [[European Union Law]] a [[European Union directive|directive]] is a form of legislative act addressed to the [[European Union member states|Member States]]. The directive binds the Member State to reach certain objectives in their national legislation.

